front.gametext: Deploy on Endor system if your biker scouts and/or AT-STs control three Endor sites. Your Force drain here is +1 for each Endor site your biker scout or AT-ST controls (limit +3). Place Effect in Used Pile if opponent controls this system. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: The Empire's remote bases develop new technology and hide sensitive projects from potential Rebel saboteurs.

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.title: •Establish Secret Base (V)
front.gametext: Deploy on Bunker if you control that site. Your Force generation at Endor system may not be canceled. Once per turn, may deploy an Endor site from your reserve deck; reshuffle. Place Effect in Used Pile if opponent controls this site. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: The Empire's remote bases develop new technology and hide sensitive projects from potential Rebel saboteurs.

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.title: •EV-9D9
front.gametext: During your control phase, may search Reserve Deck, take one power droid or Torture into hand and reshuffle. May Force drain at Droid Workshop, Droid Junkheap or Incinerator (+1 for each other droid present, including captive droids).
front.lore: MerenData EV supervisor droid. Particularly enjoys torturing power droids. A clumsy designer nearly broke this unit before it was shipped. She formerly worked at Cloud City.

front.title: Evacuate?
front.gametext: Unless Tarkin is aboard, save all characters, weapons and devices aboard any just-lost capital starship. Relocate them to any one planet site or one of your capital starships.
front.lore: Escape pods are on many starships allowing those in peril to flee, an act considered cowardly by Imperial officers. 'We've analyzed their attack, sir, and there is a danger.'

rulings: May not relocate opponent's cards.
May not relocate weapons and devices deployed directly upon a starship or vehicle (e.g. Deflector Shield Generators or Turbolaser Battery).
If relocating to a capital starship, it must have capacity for everything and all of the cards must be allowed to exist there.
If relocating to a capital starship, it must be to the starship card itself, not a starship site.

front.title: Evader
front.gametext: USED: Cancel all Revolutions in play (owner loses 1 Force for each).  LOST: If Vader or Vader's Custom TIE was just lost, relocate that card to Used Pile. OR Relocate to Used Pile one Imperial just lost from any Death Star location.
front.lore: A panic move by Black 2 send Vader spinning wildly from the Death Star trench-ironically sparing his life. His destiny would be fulfilled another time.

front.title: Evader & Monnok
front.gametext: USED: Cancel all Revolutions in play. OR If opponent has 13 or more cards in hand, place all but 8 (random selection) in Used Pile.  LOST: Use 4 Force to reveal opponent's hand. All cards opponent has two or more of in hand are lost.

rulings: The second Used function still has its result even if the opponent plays any response(s) that reduces their hand size below 13 cards.

front.title: •Executor
front.gametext: May add unlimited pilots, passengers, vehicles and starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilots aboard provide total ability of 3. Immune to attrition < 12.
front.lore: Flagship of Death Squadron. Over eight kilometers long. Carries 38,000 troops, Can conquer entire star systems by sheer intimidation and terror. Lord Vader's personal command ship.

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points
combo: Executor + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.title: •Executor: Comm Station
front.gametext: Dark:  If you occupy with Tarkin, Piett or any admiral, your starships may 'react' to same system.  Light:  If you control, your starships may 'react' from same system as Executor.

front.title: •Executor: Control Station
front.gametext: Dark:  If an Imperial leader here, Executor is power +1 for each Executor site on table.  Light:  If you control, only you may move Executor during opponent's move phase.

front.title: •Executor: Docking Bay
front.gametext: Dark:  Your docking bay transit from here is free. If you occupy, opponent may not move to this site.  Light:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 7 Force. Your transit to here requires +9 Force.

front.title: •Executor: Holotheatre
front.gametext: Dark:  If you have Vader or Emperor on table, your Force generation is +1 here (+2 if both).  Light:  If you control, Force drain +1 here.

front.title: •Executor: Main Corridor
front.gametext: Dark:  During your move phase, you may move free between here and Executor or any Executor site.  Light:  If you control, opponent's Main Corridor game text is canceled.

front.title: •Executor: Meditation Chamber
front.gametext: Dark:  If Vader alone here, once per turn, may apply his ability to draw battle destiny at any system.  Light:  If you occupy, opponent's Meditation Chamber game text is canceled.

front.title: •Exhaustion
front.gametext: Opponent must lose 1 Force for each of opponent's missing characters on table. OR Select one missing character under 'nighttime conditions' to be lost.
front.lore: 'Sir, the temperature's dropping too rapidly.' 'That's right, and my friend's out in it.'

front.title: •Expand The Empire
front.gametext: Deploy on any site. 'Expands' your 'game text' for that site to add to your 'game text' at the adjacent sites.
front.lore: The Emperor disbanded the Imperial Senate 'for the duration of the emergency,' seizing absolute power. He planned to extend rule by terrorizing planets into submission.

combo: Expand The Empire + Tatooine: Cantina + Tatooine: Lars' Moisture Farm + Tatooine: Jundland Wastes Deploy Expand The Empire at Tatooine: Lars' Moisture Farm, and it will add the gametext of that site to both adjacent sites. Now the Cantina is Force Drain +1 (making a total Force Drain of 3), and the Jundland Wastes are Force Drain +1 +1 (making a total Force Drain of 3). All this, and at all 3 sites you can add 1 to each of your weapon destiny draws.
rulings: Does not expand card titles, marker numbers, icons, or anything else besides game text.
Does not allow docking bay transit to occur to or from a non-docking bay site.
Two identical modifiers stack, for example 'Force drain +1 here. Force drain +1 here.' will work to add 2 to Force drains there.
While game text is canceled or suspended at one site, it is not expanded to adjacent sites.
Expanding the Tatooine: Podrace Arena game text to adjacent sites makes those sites non-battlegrounds while any race total > 0.

front.title: Exposure
front.gametext: Use X Force during your control phase, where X = the total number of characters present or missing at exterior marker sites under 'nighttime conditions.' Those characters are lost.
front.lore: 'Artoo says the chances of survival are 125 to 1.'

front.title: F-11D Blaster Rifle
front.gametext: Deploy on your First Order warrior. May target a character or vehicle for free. Draw destiny. Add 1 if fired by a stormtrooper. Target hit, and may not be used to satisfy attrition, if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Blank.

front.title: •Failure At The Cave
front.gametext: Deploy on Dagobah: Cave. Target an apprentice on Dagobah. All Jedi Test game text is suspended. If target present during any battle phase, opponent draws destiny. If destiny < 4, you retrieve 2 Force (also, if destiny = 0, target is lost). Otherwise, Utinni Effect canceled.
front.lore: 'That place is strong with the dark side of the Force. A domain of evil it is. In you must go.'

combo: Failure At The Cave + Dagobah: Cave

front.title: •Falleen's Fist
front.gametext: Deploys -3 if your Black Sun agent is at a related site. May add 3 pilots and 6 passengers. Permanent pilots provide total ability of 4. Immune to attrition < 8.
front.lore: Blank.

front.title: •Fanfare
front.gametext: Plays on table. Cancels Order To Engage and Scramble. Once per game you may take any Immediate Effect into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While opponent occupies no battleground systems, Staging Areas is suspended.
front.lore: The Boonta Eve crowds are always looking for new and exciting developments at every Podrace.

cards.counterpart: Don't Do That Again - Defensive Shield
cancels: Suspends Staging Areas while opponent occupies no battleground systems

front.title: •Fanfare
front.gametext: Deploy on table. Cancels Order To Engage and Scramble. Once per game you may take any Immediate Effect into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While opponent occupies no battleground systems, Staging Areas is suspended. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: The Boonta Eve crowds are always looking for new and exciting developments at every Podrace.

cancels: Suspends Staging Areas while opponent occupies not battleground systems

front.title: •Fanfare (Tatooine) (V)
front.gametext: Plays on table. Ice Storm, Lost In The Wilderness, Order To Engage, Sandwhirl, and Scramble are canceled. Once per game, may take an Immediate Effect into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Unless opponent occupies a battleground system, Staging Areas is suspended.
front.lore: The Boonta Eve crowds are always looking for new and exciting developments at every Podrace.

front.title: •Fanfare (V)
front.gametext: Plays on table. Ice Storm, Lost In The Wilderness, Order To Engage, Sandwhirl, and Scramble are canceled. Once per game, may take an Immediate Effect into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Unless opponent occupies a battleground system, Staging Areas is suspended.
front.lore: The Boonta Eve crowds are always looking for new and exciting developments at every Podrace.

cards.counterpart: Don't Do That Again (V) - Defensive Shield
cancels: Suspends Staging Areas while opponent occupies no battleground systems

front.title: •Fear
front.gametext: Opponent must choose to lose either 2 Force from hand or 1 Force from top of Reserve Deck.
front.lore: 'I'm not afraid.' 'Oh. You will be.' One of the lessons Luke learned was that fear of the unknown can be stronger than fear of the known.

front.title: •Fear Is My Ally
front.gametext: Before any starting cards are revealed, deploy on table with up to 10 cards from outside your deck face-down under here. Cards under here do not count toward your deck limit. Three times per game, may play a Defensive Shield from here, as if from hand.
front.lore: Maul's arsenal includes much more than simple combat training.

front.title: Fear Will Keep Them In Line
front.gametext: Deploy on any capital starship. When that starship is at a system or sector you control, your total power is +1 in battles at related sites.
front.lore: 'The regional governors now have direct control over their territories. Fear will keep the local systems in line. Fear of this battle station.'

combo: Fear Will Keep Them In Line + Lieutenant Venka

front.title: •Feltipern Trevagg
front.gametext: While no droid present with Trevagg, to initiate battles at same location as Trevagg, player must use X Force, where X = total number of [Dark Side Force] and [Light Side Force] present with him.
front.lore: Corrupt tax collector. A male Gotal. Bounty hunter. Once sought a bounty on Obi-Wan. Has limited sensing ability to droid emanations. Romanced M'iiyoom Onith.

canceledBy: Game text is canceled by Freon Drevan
rulings: Resets the cost of initiating battle, cannot be further modified by cards like Wars Not Make One Great.
Anything allowing battle to be initiated for free ignores this cost.
If inside a starship or enclosed vehicle, the number of Force icons present with Trevagg is 0.

front.title: •Feltipern Trevagg's Stun Rifle
front.gametext: Deploy on Feltipern Trevagg or use 2 Force to deploy on your other bounty hunter. May target a character using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Add 2 if target is the target of any bounty. Target may be captured if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Assault rifle modified by Feltipern. Used by the Gotal bounty hunter before he became a tax collector. Occasionally brought along to 'ease' Feltipern's collection duties.

front.title: Field Promotion
front.gametext: Deploy on an Imperial of ability < 5 present with Vader, Emperor or one of your admirals, generals, or moffs. Imperial gains {leader} skill, is power +1, and is immune to Demotion, Report to Lord Vader, and What is Thy Bidding, My Master? (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Imperial officers are fiercely competitive, especially on the Executor. Lord Vader's flagship is a place where devious political calculation prospers. The naive are doomed to failure.

front.title: •Fighter Cover
front.gametext: Each starfighter that fires a weapon in battle is power +3 for the remainder of battle. Once per turn you may cancel and redraw your starship weapon destiny just drawn. At sites related to systems you occupy, your characters who have immunity to attrition each add 2 to immunity and 1 to each of that character's weapon destiny draws.

front.title: •Fighters Coming In
front.gametext: Unique (•) starfighters without permanent pilots are immune to attrition < 4 (or add 2 to immunity if starfighter already has immunity). Starships without pilot characters aboard are power -2. At docking bays related to systems you occupy, your Force drains are +1. Once per turn, your starfighter just lost from a system may be relocated to a related docking bay.

front.title: •Fighters Straight Ahead
front.gametext: Deploy on table. Your Force generation is +1 at systems you control. Opponent's non-unique starfighters are deploy +1 (or +2 to a system you occupy). (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Sometimes a swarm of starfighters can look more imposing than it really is. Mostly though, it's just best to avoid them altogether.

front.title: •Finalizer
front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, and 4 [First Order] starfighters. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Deploys -4 to [Episode VII] systems and adds 1 to your Force drains there. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Blank.

front.title: •Firepower
front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Each of your starships with two or more starship weapons aboard is power +2. Once during each of your deploy phases, you may use 2 Force to deploy from Lost Pile one starship weapon, vehicle weapon or artillery weapon (for free).
front.lore: 'About twenty guns. Some on the surface, some on the towers.'

pulls: vehicle weapon or artillery weapon from Lost Pile to deploy it for free

front.title: •••First Order Special Forces TIE
front.gametext: May add 1 pilot and 1 passenger. Matching starfighter for any First Order pilot of ability < 3. Power +1 at opponent's system. While matching pilot aboard, immune to attrition < 3.
front.lore: Blank.

front.title: First Order Stormtrooper
front.gametext: Deploys -1 to same site as a First Order leader. Opponent's characters here are cumulatively defense value -1 (limit -3).
front.lore: Blank.

front.title: •First Strike
front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Whenever a battle is initiated, player initiating battle retrieves 1 Force and defender loses 1 Force. Also, during a battle you initiate, each time opponent plays an interrupt, opponent must first use 1 Force. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'There'll be no escape for the princess this time.'

combo: First Strike + Jawa Pack (Pschobabble)

front.title: •Flagship
front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer. Your other starships may move as a 'react' to same system or sector (for free). If starship lost, you lose X Force, where X = starship's armor. (Immune to your Alter.)
front.lore: After the Battle of Yavin, it was politically necessary to demonstrate the unstoppable might of the Empire. The Executor and Death Squadron ensured this objective.

combo: Flagship + Alert My Star Destroyer!

front.title: •Flagship Executor
front.gametext: May add unlimited pilots, passengers and starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 3. Immune to attrition if target of Flagship Operations.
front.lore: Command ship of the Imperial Fleet at the Battle of Endor. Originally constructed at the Fondor shipyards. Admiral Piett stationed aboard.

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points
combo: Flagship Executor + Flagship Operations
Flagship Executor + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
Flagship Executor + Alert My Star Destroyer! Make Flagship Executor immune to attrition by shuttling your commander, moff or Dark Jedi aboard.

front.title: •Flagship Operations
front.gametext: Deploy on any Star Destroyer if at least 5 Executor sites on table. Your TIEs are deploy -1, forfeit +2 and destiny +2. At systems where you have a TIE, your Imperial capital starships are deploy -3 and your battle destiny draws are +1 each. (If on Executor, immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'There's too many of them!'

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points
combo: Flagship Operations + Flagship Executor

front.title: Flare-S Racing Swoop
front.gametext: May add 1 driver and 1 passenger. Landspeed = driver's ability, and may be used at any time to follow an opponent's vehicle or character that just moved from same site (if within range).
front.lore: Attain speeds of up to 600 kph. 3 meters long. Extremely difficult to control at high speeds. Dengar rode a similar swoop when injured in a race with Han at Agrilat.

front.title: •Flawless Marksmanship
front.gametext: Add X to one starship weapon or tractor beam destiny (before destiny is drawn) when targeting opponent's starship.USED: X = 2.  LOST: X = 4.
front.lore: Heavy-weapons gunners assigned to Imperial facilities undergo intense training. The Imperial Navy boasts a higher weapons accuracy rate than that of the Imperial Army.

combo: Flawless Marksmanship + Tractor Beam

front.title: •Flight Escort
front.gametext: During your move phase, if you have at least two combat vehicles at same cloud sector, relocate one starfighter present to a related docking bay or system. OR If one of your combat vehicles is defending a battle at a cloud sector, add one battle destiny.
front.lore: 'Rather touchy, aren't they?'

front.title: ••Floating Refinery
front.gametext: Deploy on a cloud sector (limit one per sector). Force you activate may be drawn into hand (one per turn for each of your Floating Refineries on table). Each cloud sector or gas miner drawn in this way by this device may be revealed to retrieve 1 Force.
front.lore: Refines Tibanna gas at mines like those at Cloud City. Also used for moisture collection on dry planets.

front.title: •FN-2003
front.gametext: Once per turn, if with your First Order trooper, may use 1 Force to target opponent's character present (free if Finn) and make FN-2003 'hit;' for remainder of turn, target's game text is canceled and target may not fire weapons.
front.lore: Stormtrooper.

front.title: •FN-2199 (Nines)
front.gametext: During battle with a stormtrooper, may cancel one opponent's just drawn automated or lightsaber weapon destiny. Permanent weapon is Z6 Riot Control Baton (may target a character for free; draw destiny; target hit if destiny > defense value).
front.lore: Stormtrooper.

front.title: •Focused Attack
front.gametext: If Vader is present during a battle at a site, for remainder of turn, he loses his immunity to attrition, but adds ability to power (he may not apply ability toward drawing battle destiny). OR During a duel, add one destiny to your total.
front.lore: Not since his duel with Obi-Wan had Vader unleashed the raw power of the dark side.

front.title: •Fondor
front.gametext: Dark:  Executor deploys -5 here. If you occupy, all opponent's Corellian corvettes are forfeit -4 and deploy +1.  Light:  Force drain -1 here. If you control, opponent may not deploy Executor.

front.title: •Force Field
front.gametext: USED: Cancel an attempt to target a Dark Jedi with a character weapon.  LOST: If one of your characters was just targeted by a weapon during a battle, use 3 Force to cancel the targeting.
front.lore: Han was fast. Vader was faster.

cancels: An attempt to target a Dark Jedi with a character weapon
Targeting of a character by a weapon

front.title: •Force Field (V)
front.gametext: USED: Cancel an attempt to use a character weapon to target your character of ability > 4.  LOST: Use 2 Force to cancel an attempt to use a [Permanent Weapon] weapon to target your character.
front.lore: Han was fast. Vader was faster.

cancels: An attempt to use a character weapon to target your character of ability > 4
An attempt to use a [Permanent] weapon to target your character

front.title: •Force Freeze
front.gametext: USED: Cancel the game text of a character of ability < 5 present with Kylo for remainder of turn.LOST: If a battle was just initiated where there are no smugglers, take the first weapons segment action (or first two if you initiated).
front.lore: Blank.

front.title: •Force Lightning
front.gametext: USED: Target any character (even a captive) present with Emperor. Target is defense value -4 for remainder of turn.  LOST: Emperor loses immunity to attrition and is defense value -2 for remainder of turn. Draw destiny. Target lost if destiny +1 > defense value.
front.lore: The Emperor is strong in the dark arts of the Force. He can direct pure energy to shoot forth from his outstretched fingers.

rulings: May not target a frozen captive.

front.title: Force Pike
front.gametext: Deploy on your Royal Guard (or use 3 Force to deploy on your other warrior). Adds 1 to defense value. May target a character or creature using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value. If hit by a Royal Guard, target's power = 0.
front.lore: Uses microscopic vibrations emitted from its tip. Cuts through stone, metal, and bone. Ceremonial weapon for most; deadly implement in the hands of an Emperor's Royal Guard.

front.title: •Force Push
front.gametext: Target opponent's Jedi with at least one combat card present with your Dark Jedi. Reveal one of target's combat cards (random selection). If revealed card's destiny > 4, place it on top of opponent's Reserve Deck. Otherwise, lose 1 Force. (Immune to Sense.)
front.lore: A fully-trained Sith warrior has more weapons at his disposal than just a lightsaber.

rulings: If the revealed card is destiny 4 or less, it is un-revealed and placed back under the Jedi.

front.title: •Force Push (V)
front.gametext: Once per game, choose: during battle, use 2 Force to target your Dark Jedi and opponent's character of equal or lesser ability present. Both targets are excluded from battle. OR Exchange two cards from hand with any one card from Force Pile; reshuffle.
front.lore: A fully-trained Sith warrior has more weapons at his disposal than just a lightsaber.

front.title: •Forced Landing
front.gametext: Deploy on a docking bay. Target an opponent's starfighter at the related system or a related cloud sector. Target may not move away from Utinni Effect. Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.
front.lore: 'You will not deviate from your present course. . . Permission granted to land on platform three-two-seven.'

rulings: The targeted starfighter may not move (or be carried) to any system, asteroid sector, or Death Star II sector.
The targeted starfighter may not move (or be carried) to any cloud sector of higher altitude.
The targeted starfighter may not move (or be carried) to any site except the site where Forced Landing is deployed.

front.title: •Forced Servitude
front.gametext: Deploy on an opponent's location. Whenever you lose a droid from hand or Life Force, it satisfies Force loss up to its forfeit value. Once per turn, you may play Imperial Code Cylinder to cancel a Force drain where you have a droid. Effect canceled if opponent controls this location.
front.lore: The Empire often uses droids for nefarious purposes. Imperials compel droids to do jobs that are repugnant to humans. An automaton has no ethical conscience.

front.title: <>Forest
front.gametext: Dark:  May not deploy to Bespin, Coruscant, Hoth, Kessel or Tatooine. Your characters present here are immune to attrition.  Light:  May not deploy to Bespin, Coruscant, Hoth, Kessel or Tatooine.

front.title: •Fozec
front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While at a site you control, Imperials are immune to Ke Chu Ke Kukuta? at that site.
front.lore: Spy for the Empire. Keeping tabs on Jabba's activities for the ISB. Secretly hoping to leave the Empire and pursue lucrative opportunities in the underworld.

combo: Fozec + Nevar Yalnal

front.title: •Freeze!
front.gametext: If a Rebel just deployed or moved to a site where you have a trooper present armed with a weapon, use 1 Force. For remainder of turn, that Rebel may not battle or move and battle damage against you is limited to 4 at that location.
front.lore: Despite Wicket's warnings, an Imperial scout got the drop on Leia.

front.title: •Frostbite
front.gametext: Deploy on Hoth system. At the end of each player's turn, for every character that player has present at a marker site under 'nighttime conditions,' that player must lose 1 Force (2 if character is missing).
front.lore: 'Luke! Luke! Don't do this. C'mon, gimme a sign here.'

front.title: Frozen Dinner
front.gametext: Deploy on opponent's character alone at Wampa Cave. Character is power = 0 and may not move. May be canceled if opponent has a lightsaber or total ability > 4 present. If character eaten by a creature, cumulatively adds 2 to ferocity.
front.lore: Freeze dried and ready to serve, a tasty, wholesome Rebel makes a nutritious meal for the whole wampa clan. They're Gr-r-reat!

front.title: •Frustration
front.gametext: During your control phase, peek at opponent's hand and target one non-Interrupt card you find there that has a deploy cost < total number of [Light Side] icons on table. Opponent must deploy a card of that title by the end of your next turn, or lose a card of that title from hand (if possible).
front.lore: 'Rrraaaarrr!'

front.title: Full Scale Alert
front.gametext: Use 2 Force. Draw Destiny. If destiny < number of Stormtroopers on the table, all opponent's movement is blocked for the remainder of this turn (except for smugglers and the starships they are aboard).
front.lore: Imperial stormtroopers adopt strict security measures. Excellent communications and sheer numbers can hinder Rebel movement across entire territories.

rulings: The phrase 'movement is blocked' means the cards cannot move.

front.title: Furry Fury
front.gametext: USED: Cancel Wookiee Roar or Han's Back or Life Debt.  LOST: If Han and Chewie are in a battle together, draw two destiny. Subtract total from opponent's attrition and total power (cannot fall below zero).
front.lore: 'All right, don't lose your temper.' Hoth hath no fury like a Wookiee scorned.

front.title: Fusion Generator Supply Tanks
front.gametext: Deploy on your starship at a system or sector where a related docking bay is on table. Adds 1 to hyperspeed, power and maneuver.
front.lore: Installed at many facilities throughout the Empire to provide power to the Imperial spacefleet. Supplies starships with energy necessary for sublight and hyperspace travel.

front.title: FX-10 (Effex-ten)
front.gametext: Once per turn, one of your 'hit' non-droid characters at same or adjacent site may go to your Used Pile rather than your Lost Pile.
front.lore: Standard medical droid used by Imperial field units. Enhanced programming allows FX-10 to treat a wide variety of battle wounds.

front.title: Gaderffii Stick
front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Tusken Raider. If a battle has just been initiated where present, target a character for free; draw two destiny. If total destiny > 5, target's weapons are 'knocked away' (may not be used this battle).
front.lore: Notorious 'gaffi' weapon favored by Tusken Raiders. Built from scavenged metal. Intimidates and evokes fear.

front.title: •Gailid
front.gametext: Deploys free to same site as Mosep. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While at Audience Chamber, adds 1 to your Force drains at Jabba's Palace sites.
front.lore: Mosep's assistant. Accountant. Tax collector. Enjoys tending to Jabba's skiffs with Barada.

combo: Gailid + Mosep
canceledBy: Game text canceled by Freon Drevan if at same or adjacent site

front.title: •Gall
front.gametext: Dark:  While you occupy, once per battle you may choose a target just 'hit' by a blaster or rifle (except Permanent weapons) to be lost.  Light:  Immune to Revolution.

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.title: •Gamall Wironicc
front.gametext: Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. While Gamall is in battle, your other characters present with him may not be targeted by opponent's weapons. Place Gamall in Used Pile if he was just 'hit.' Power -2 while on Tatooine.
front.lore: Strange wanderer. Rumored to have sacrificed himself in battle so that his comrades could live on. Survived and now stranded on Tatooine. He misses everything he'll never be.

combo: Gamall Wironicc + Chokk Power 11 while defending a battle and they double the weapons protection for your characters.

front.title: Gamorrean Ax
front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your Gamorrean. Adds 1 to power. When present at a site, Gamorrean draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. May target a character or creature for free. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Built by Snogrutt, a Gamorrean engineer. Ax head contains an ultrasonic generator. Jabba's Gamorrean guards sometimes switch the power off to prove their might.

front.title: Gamorrean Guard
front.gametext: Deploys only to Tatooine. Power -1 when not at a Tatooine site. May be sacrificed (lost) to cancel an attack just initiated by a creature present.
front.lore: Big. Strong. Dumb.

front.title: •Gardulla The Hutt
front.gametext: When you retrieve Force from Boonta Eve Podrace, any or all of your retrieved Force may be taken into hand. Once during your control phase, may use 1 Force; opponent draws one destiny. If destiny > 2, you retrieve 1 Force. Otherwise, lose 1 Force.
front.lore: Well-known as a gambler and a gangster. Gardulla was a former owner of Shmi and Anakin Skywalker, before losing them in a bet to the Toydarian junk dealer, Watto.

front.title: •Garindan
front.gametext: When at same location as a Rebel of ability > 2, deploy -1 there for any Imperials, and during your move phase, Imperials at an adjacent site may move there for free.
front.lore: Long-nosed, male Kubaz from Kubindi. Spy. Squealed on Obi-Wan and Luke outside Docking Bay 94. Works for Jabba the Hutt or the highest bidder. Not particularly brave.

combo: Garindan + Nevar Yalnal

front.title: •Gela Yeens
front.gametext: May deploy for free to your [Independent Starship] starship. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Power +2 when present with and opponent's smuggler. When targeted by a weapon, subtract one from each weapon destiny.
front.lore: Bad-tempered smuggler. Makes a few credits more helping Jabba collect debts. Highly regarded for his uncanny anticipation in battle. Searching for Debnoli.

rulings: Does not subtract 1 from Thermal Detonator weapon destiny draws.

front.title: •General Grievous
front.gametext: Any stolen lightsaber may deploy on Grievous. Once per game, Grievous may steal a lightsaber from opponent's Lost Pile. Unless alone, may lose 1 Force to return Grievous (and your cards on him) to hand from a site you control. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Trade Federation.

pulls: Steals one lightsaber from opponent's lost pile

front.title: •General Grievous (AI)
front.gametext: Any stolen lightsaber may deploy on Grievous. Once per game, Grievous may steal a lightsaber from opponent's Lost Pile. Unless alone, may lose 1 Force to return Grievous (and your cards on him) to hand from a site you control. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Trade Federation.

front.title: •General Grievous (OAI)
front.gametext: Any stolen lightsaber may deploy on Grievous. Once per game, Grievous may steal a lightsaber from opponent's Lost Pile. Unless alone, may lose 1 Force to return Grievous (and your cards on him) to hand from a site you control. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Trade Federation.

front.title: •General Hux
front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. Deploys -2 aboard Finalizer. Your First Order characters and [First Order] starships are destiny +1. Once per game, may take a First Order stormtrooper into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Leader.

front.title: •General Nevar
front.gametext: Adds 2 to the power of anything he pilots (3 if Blizzard 2). Deploys -1 to Hoth. When deployed, may peek at top card of any Reserve Deck. When a spy here is targeted by Trample, adds 1 to your destiny draw.
front.lore: ISB leader.

front.title: •General Tagge
front.gametext: Tagge's forfeit +1 for each Imperial trooper, of any kind, present with him at a site.
front.lore: Oversees defense operations of Death Star. Outstanding tactician. No-nonsense leader. Member of the House of Tagge, a powerful noble family and corporate conglomerate.

combo: General Tagge + Lone Warrior Add two battle destinies if General Tagge is defending a battle alone at a site.
General Tagge + Commander Igar When Commander Igar is in battle with Tagge, may use 2 Force to cancel and redraw one just-drawn battle destiny.

front.title: •General Veers
front.gametext: Power +1 when at same site as Admiral Ozzel. Adds 1 to power of each Imperial at same Hoth site. Adds 3 to power of any combat vehicle he pilots. On Blizzard 1, also adds 1 to armor and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: General Maximillian Veers is the model of Imperial Army officer. Cunning, loyal and ruthlessly efficient leader. In charge of the ground assault troops in Vader's forces.

front.title: •General Veers (V)
front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots.  While piloting an AT-AT, draws two battle destiny if unable to otherwise.  While piloting a combat vehicle, its immunity to attrition is +2.
front.lore: General Maximillian Veers is the model of Imperial Army officer. Cunning, loyal and ruthlessly efficient leader. In charge of the ground assault troops in Vader's forces.

combo: General Veers (V) + Commander Igar When in battle with Veers or Tagge, Commander Igar may use 2 Force to cancel and redraw one just-drawn battle destiny.

front.title: •Ghana Gleemort
front.gametext: Your Force generation at same site is +X, where X equals the number of opponent's aliens at same and adjacent sites. May lose 1 Force to cancel a Force drain at an adjacent site.
front.lore: Part of Jabba's Gamorrean security force. Negotiating with the B'omarr monks regarding his possible defection.

cancels: A Force drain at an adjacent site

front.title: Ghhhk
front.gametext: During the damage segment of a battle you lost, if you have no cards left that can be forfeited, cancel all remaining battle damage. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel Nightfall.
front.lore: Dejarik of creature from Clak'dor VII. Ghhhk rise with the dawn, screeching their mating calls across the jungle. Locals use their skin oils as a healing salve.

combo: Ghhhk + Imperial Holotable + Mosep Mosep should be one of the prime force drain members, as the loss will come straight from the Light Side Reserve Deck.

Ghhhk + Sunsdown + Defel Defel under 'night time conditions' fits the theme of this deck perfectly, as he can avoid combat, thus saving the use of the Ghhhk, and still be there for the counter attack.
cancels: All remaining battle damage if you just forfeited all cards that participated in a battle you lost

front.title: Ghhhk & Those Rebels Won't Escape Us
front.gametext: USED: Cancel Nabrun Leids.  LOST: If you just forfeited all your cards that participated in a battle you lost, cancel all remaining battle damage (Immune to Sense). OR Cancel Hyper Escape, Closer!?, or one 'react.' OR During your move phase, cancel Landing Claw.

front.title: •Giran
front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Power +3 when defending a battle at a Jabba's Palace site. May forfeit in place of one of your alien leaders present who was 'hit' by a weapon, restoring that leader to normal.
front.lore: Kajain'sa'Nikto. Loyal to Jabba. Helps tend the rancor with Malakili. Hopes to snare a krayt dragon someday and pit it against the rancor.

front.title: •Go For Help!
front.gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle at an exterior site with double your total power, reveal top 3 cards of your Reserve Deck. If any of those cards are scouts or speeder bikes, deploy them for free to that battle (replace others on top of Reserve Deck in same order).
front.lore: When confronted with enemy troops, biker scouts are instructed to immediately call for reinforcements.

rulings: The revealed cards may be deployed in any order.

front.title: •Gragra
front.gametext: Once per turn, may use 1 Force to target opponent's card with ability just deployed to same site. Opponent must use 2 Force or return target to hand. Power +2 at Mos Espa.
front.lore: Female Swokes Swokes. Lives in the city of Mos Espa and runs a street-corner market there. Seller of chuba.

front.title: •Grand Admiral Thrawn
front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any starship he pilots. When piloting a star destroyer in battle, adds one battle destiny. While no other admiral and no star cruiser on table, your Admiral's Order just placed in Used Pile from table, may be taken into hand instead.
front.lore: The last remaining Grand Admiral. Found legendary Katana fleet of missing dreadnaughts. Military genius. Master of unorthodox tactics. Passionate collector of art. Leader.

combo: Grand Admiral Thrawn + Captain Gilad Pellaeon Captain Gilad Pellaeon deploys free to Thrawn's location.
Grand Admiral Thrawn at a system + Imperial Command

front.title: •Grand Admiral Thrawn (V)
front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any starship he pilots. if a Rebel just moved from here, your Imperials present may follow that character (using landspeed). While at a battleground site, functions as a general and game text of Admiral's Orders is suspended.
front.lore: The last remaining Grand Admiral. Found legendary Katana fleet of missing dreadnaughts. Military genius. Master of unorthodox tactics. Passionate collector of art. Leader.

combo: Grand Admiral Thrawn at a system or site + Imperial Command

front.title: •Grand Moff Tarkin
front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When with Vader in a battle, once per battle may cancel one opponent's destiny just drawn.
front.lore: Leader. Governor of Outer Rim Territories. Commanded Death Star. Helped disband Imperial Senate. Defined doctrine of rule by fear. Plotted to use Death Star against Emperor.

combo: Grand Moff Tarkin + any Darth Vader persona
cancels: One opponent's destiny just drawn when in battle with Vader
rulings: May cancel any type of destiny such as battle destiny, weapon destiny, Sense destiny, etc.
May cancel a duel destiny (if the duel takes place during a battle where Tarkin is with Vader).

front.title: •Grand Moff Tarkin (V)
front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Destiny +2 when drawn for destiny. Draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise (if with Vader or an Imperial leader, may add one instead). During battle, if you just drew a destiny < number of Imperials here, may cancel and redraw that destiny.
front.lore: Leader. Governor of Outer Rim Territories. Commanded Death Star. Helped disband Imperial Senate. Defined doctrine of rule by fear. Plotted to use Death Star against Emperor.

rulings: If he adds a battle destiny, he can no longer draw one battle destiny if unable to otherwise that battle.

front.title: Gravel Storm
front.gametext: Strikes at Dune Sea, Jundland Wastes, Beggar's Canyon, Lars' Moisture Farm, Jawa Camp, or Mos Eisley. Target opponent's character present at that site. Draw destiny. Target lost if destiny > ability.
front.lore: Tatooine's twin suns cause turbulent storms that strike with little or no warning. Strong winds whip rocks through the air with enormous force.

front.title: •Gravity Shadow
front.gametext: If opponent's starship has just begun to move through hyperspace, draw destiny. If destiny > pilot's ability, starship must return to original location and may not move this turn. If destiny = pilot's ability, starship is lost.
front.lore: 'Traveling through hyperspace ain't like dustin' crops, boy!' Gravitational phenomena cast shadows in hyperspace, posing a serious threat to lightspeed navigation.

rulings: Can be played as a response to any hyperspace movement, including (for example) Hyper Escape.
Targets both the starship and the highest ability pilot (either a permanent pilot or a character who is piloting).
If multiple permanent pilots and/or character pilots are tied for highest ability, Dark chooses one to target.
For Han, Chewie, And The Falcon, targets Han's 3 ability.

front.title: •Greeata
front.gametext: Other Rodians deploy -1 to same site. Once during each of your control phases, may use 1 Force to take any Rodian into hand from Reserve Deck- reshuffle. While at Audience Chamber, all your other musicians are deploy -1 and forfeit +3.
front.lore: Rodian musician. In addition to her singing talents, she plays kloo horn. Befriended Sy Snootles on the luxury liner Kuari Princess.

front.title: •Greedo
front.gametext: During opponent's control phase, may 'threaten' one smuggler at same site. Opponent may use all Force Pile cards to cancel threat, allowing you to activate same amount. Otherwise, draw destiny. If destiny + Greedo's ability > 6, smuggler lost.
front.lore: Male Rodian bounty hunter. Sent by Jabba to capture Han. Arrogant, overconfident and not too bright. Trained by bounty hunters Nataz and Goa, who betrayed him to Thuku.

front.title: •Greedo (V)
front.gametext: May deploy as a 'react.' Opponent must first use 1 Force to fire a weapon at same site. Weapons fired using Sorry About The Mess must target Greedo (if possible). Nabrun Leids may not transport characters to or from here.
front.lore: Male Rodian bounty hunter. Sent by Jabba to capture Han. Arrogant, overconfident and not too bright. Trained by bounty hunters Nataz and Goa, who betrayed him to Thuku.

front.title: •Grotto Werribee
front.gametext: Deploys -1 to a docking bay. Adds 2 to the power of anything he pilots. While at opponent's docking bay, adds 2 to your Force drains there, and your vehicles and other characters there are immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Once a junior traffic controller for an interstellar shipping corporation, Grotto brags that there is nothing about docking bay procedure that he doesn't know. Information broker.

front.title: •Guri
front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything she pilots. When present with Xizor, he may not be targeted by weapons. While Vader not here, opponent may draw no more than one battle destiny here. Immune to purchase, Restraining Bolt, and attrition < 5.
front.lore: Human-replica droid. Programmed to function as Xizor's personal bodyguard and assassin. Black Sun agent. Cost 9 million credits. Worth every decicred.

front.title: •Halt!
front.gametext: During any deploy phase, target a character at same site as your battle droid. Target is landspeed = 0 for remainder of turn. OR If opponent just deployed a character to same site as your battle droid, opponent must use 1 Force or place that character in hand.
front.lore: 'Coruscant?'

front.title: Han Seeker
front.gametext: Deploys for 1 Force to an unoccupied site. Deploys and moves like an undercover spy. When present with Han (or alien) of ability < 3, choose one to be immediately lost (treat as an 'all cards' situation). Seeker is also lost.
front.lore: Military version of a 'remote.' Programmed to stalk specific targets or secondary targets. Heat and light sensors track with fatal accuracy. Can stow away on starships.

front.title: He Hasn't Come Back Yet
front.gametext: During your control phase, target any character alone at one of your exterior planet sites (except a docking bay). Draw destiny. Target is missing if destiny + 3 > ability.
front.lore: 'Princess Leia is wondering about Master Luke...She doesn't know where he is.' 'I don't know where he is.' 'Nobody knows where he is.'

rulings: The site must have been deployed by the player playing this Interrupt.
May target a character aboard a starship or vehicle. If successful, the character is removed from the starship or vehicle and becomes missing at that site.

front.title: •He Is Not Ready
front.gametext: Deploy on any character. Subtracts 2 from that character's training destiny draws. OR Deploy on an opponent's pilot at a site. During each of opponent's move phases, opponent must choose to move that character, lose that character or lose 1 Force.
front.lore: 'All his live has he looked away. To the future, to the horizon. Never his mind on where he was! Hmm? What he was doing! Hm.'

rulings: Both functions deploy only on a character card (not on a permanent pilot).
Per errata, this card is unique (•).

front.title: Heart Of The Chasm
front.gametext: During your deploy phase, use X Force to rearrange all Cloud City sites, where X = total number of those sites. All cards at a given site move along with that site. OR Cancel Off The Edge. OR Search your Reserve Deck, take one Weather Vane into hand and reshuffle.
front.lore: The Cloud City chasm's central fin was engineered with a tensile strength unsurpassed by anything in the region, save the silk of the Kashyyyk treeworm.

front.title: Heavy Fire Zone
front.gametext: If a battle was just initiated, deploy (for free) a vehicle weapon or starship weapon from hand (or Reserve Deck; reshuffle) on your participating vehicle or starship.
front.lore: 'Heavy fire boss! Twenty-three degrees.'

pulls: A vehicle or starship weapon for free during battle

front.title: Heavy Turbolaser Battery
front.gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy in your Star Destroyer (adds 2 to power) or any mobile system. May target a starship using 2 Force. Draw two destiny. Subtract 1 when targeting a capital starship. Otherwise, subtract 6. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: The ultimate in armor penetration. Relies in dense capacitor banks for massive firing charge. Capacitors regularly malfunction. Hitting maneuverable targets nearly impossible.

front.title: •Hem Dazon
front.gametext: Once during each of your deploy phases, may place, face down, one card from hand or Force Pile under Hem, as 'salt consumption.' If Hem lost, cards underneath also lost. *Power = 1 + number of cards underneath.
front.lore: Male scout from Cona. As with many Arconas, Hem has succumbed to the power of salt, and addiction indicated by his gold eye color.

front.title: •Herat
front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. During your control phase may search Reserve Deck, take 1 Utinni! or Jawa into hand and reshuffle. If you have 3 or more Jawas on table, may play Utinni! to cancel a Force drain at a related site or to cancel Control.
front.lore: Female Jawa shaman. Advised Wittin during his plotting with Jabba. Agreed to fan the Hutt in return for his cooperation to help usurp Kalit.

front.title: •Hermi Odle
front.gametext: When in a battle, you may 'react' by deploying any one non-unique blaster (for free) on Hermi from Reserve Deck. reshuffle. When present with your Advosze at a site, allows your character weapons to transfer for free there.
front.lore: Baragwin assigned by Jabba to be the palace's master weaponsmith. Enemy of Pote Snitkin.

front.title: He's All Yours, Bounty Hunter
front.gametext: USED: Cancel Captive Pursuit.  LOST: During your move phase, transfer an escorted captive to another bounty hunter or warrior present.
front.lore: Once Skywalker had taken the bait, Han was of no use to the Empire.

front.title: He's All Yours, Bounty Hunter (V)
front.gametext: USED: For remainder of turn, your bounty hunter draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise and moves for free during your move phase. LOST: Cancel an attempt to use a weapon to target your bounty hunter escorting a captive.
front.lore: Once Skywalker had taken the bait, Han was of no use to the Empire.

front.title: •Hidden Weapons
front.gametext: If Boba Fett, or your character with Mandalorian Armor is present during the weapons phase of a battle, target one opponent's character present. Draw Destiny: (0-1) no effect (2-3) character immediately captured (4-5) character is hit (6+) character immediately lost.
front.lore: Boba Fett's Mandalorian armor was so versatile that his opponents never knew what to expect.

pulledBy: Quick Reflexes when in Lost Pile
rulings: The text 'Mandalorian Armor' refers only to the device with that exact card title, not to lore.

front.title: •High Anxiety
front.gametext: If an opponent's character with ability > 2 has just become missing, deploy on a Rebel with ability > 2 on same planet. Rebel may not participate in battle. Immediate Effect canceled if missing character is found or lost.
front.lore: When a Rebel is missing, ranking members of the Alliance express a professional yet dispassionate concern. Some are not so dispassionate.

rulings: This card is canceled if the missing character is no longer missing (found, captured, leaves table, etc).

front.title: •High-speed Tactics
front.gametext: Target two non-creature vehicles with maneuver (one yours, one opponent's) present at same site. Both players draw destiny, add your vehicle's maneuver to your total. Lowest total loses vehicle. OR You speeder bike piloted by a biker scout adds one battle destiny.
front.lore: Biker scouts train relentlessly on their speeder bikes to ensure that their speed advantage is a potent weapon. This training includes highvelocity brawling.

front.title: •His Name Is Anakin
front.gametext: Deploy on table. Each non-battleground docking bay generates no more than one Force for either player. Opponent's aliens deploy +1 on Tatooine (or +2 if non-unique or to same Tatooine site as your Dark Jedi, or +4 if both). (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Anakin dreamt that one day he would return to Tatooine to free the slaves. His aggression will one day be felt by the entire Republic.

front.title: •Hit Racer
front.gametext: During your control phase, use 2 Force to target opponent's Podracer with a race total within 4 of one of your race totals. Draw destiny. If destiny > target Podracer's destiny number, opponent may not draw race destiny this turn and target Podracer is 'damaged.'
front.lore: Sebulba is willing to utilize a variety of 'tactics' to maintain his lead position. Mars Guo learned this lesson the hard way.

front.title: ••HoloNet Transmission
front.gametext: USED: Cancel Transmission Terminated.  LOST: Take one Imperial or Visage Of The Emperor into hand from Used Pile; reshuffle.
front.lore: The Empire uses a real-time hologram communication network. Provides extensive coordination in battles, blockades and searches. Allows rapid deployment and reinforcement.

pulls: Visage Of The Emperor from Used Pile

front.title: •Homing Beacon
front.gametext: Deploy on opponent's starship (even if 'concealed') if your bounty hunter or Imperial leader is on table. Your starships may move for free (and may move as a 'react') to this location. During your move phase, may cancel Landing Claw on this starship.
front.lore: 'You're sure the homing beacon is secure aboard their ship? I'm taking an awful risk, Vader. This had better work.'

front.title: •Hondo Ohnaka
front.gametext: Draws one battle destiny in not able to otherwise. While at Audience Chamber (or stacked on your Objective), your other Weequays are deploy -1, power +1, and forfeit +2. Once per game, may deploy Aurra Sing, Slave I, or a Kowakian from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Weequay gangster, leader, and pirate.

front.title: •Hot Pursuit
front.gametext: USED: If opponent's card present with your vehicle of landspeed > 2 has just begun to move as a 'react', cancel that 'react'.  LOST: Select one opponent's vehicle present with your vehicle of landspeed > 2 to be power = 0 for remainder of turn.
front.lore: The mobility of speeder bikes is greatly valued by the Empire's advanced scout detachments.

front.title: •Hoth
front.gametext: Dark:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Hoth sites.  Light:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Hoth sites.

front.title: •Hoth: Defensive Perimeter (3rd Marker)
front.gametext: Dark:  Add 1 to each of your weapon destiny draws here. If you control, Force drain +1 here.  Light:  Your troopers are forfeit -1 here.

front.title: •Hoth: Echo Command Center (War Room)
front.gametext: Dark:  Add 1 to total of Commence Primary Ignition when targeting the Hoth system.  Light:  If you control, your starship movement from Hoth sites to the Hoth system is free.

front.title: •Hoth: Echo Corridor
front.gametext: Dark:  If you occupy, you may raise all of your converted Hoth locations to the top.  Light:

front.title: •Hoth: Echo Docking Bay
front.gametext: Dark:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 2 Force.  Light:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.

front.title: •Hoth: Ice Plains (5th Marker)
front.gametext: Dark:  During your move phase, you may move free from here directly to Mountains (or vice versa).  Light:  If you control, and Main Power Generators on table, Force drain -1 here.

front.title: •Hoth: Ice Plains (5th Marker) (V)
front.gametext: Dark:  Once per game, may exchange an Interrupt from hand with bottom card of your Reserve Deck.  Light:  Ice Storm is canceled at Hoth sites.

front.title: •Hoth: Mountains (6th Marker)
front.gametext: Dark:  Your Imperials and combat vehicles deploy -1 here.  Light:  If you control, Force drain +1 here.

front.title: •Hoth: North Ridge (4th Marker)
front.gametext: Dark:  Your AT-ATs move to here for free.  Light:

front.title: •Hoth: Wampa Cave (7th Marker)
front.gametext: Dark:  Your Wampas deploy free here.  Light:  If you control, and Main Power Generators on table, Force drain -1 here.

front.title: •Hound's Tooth
front.gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be smuggler or bounty hunter), 6 passengers and 1 vehicle. Immune to attrition < 4 if Bossk piloting. Deploys and moves like a starfighter. Has ship-docking capability.
front.lore: Controlled by state-of-the-art-voice-activated X10-D computers. Internal sensors and security systems monitor prisoner activity. Modified for Bossk's Trandoshan physiology.

front.title: •Hound's Tooth (V)
front.gametext: May add 1 alien pilot, 6 passengers, and 1 vehicle. Deploys (even using Combat Response) and moves like a starfighter. While Bossk piloting, adds one battle destiny and immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Controlled by state-of-the-art-voice-activated X10-D computers. Internal sensors and security systems monitor prisoner activity. Modified for Bossk's Trandoshan physiology.

front.title: Human Shield
front.gametext: USED: If an opponent's weapon is about to 'hit' an Imperial present with a captive being escorted, the captive is 'hit' instead.  LOST: During the damage segment of a battle at a site, you may forfeit any captives present (once per battle per captive).
front.lore: A shining example of Imperial honor and bravery.

rulings: For the Used function, any weapon results that would have affected the Imperial affect the captive instead.
Weapon results that don't affect a specific character (such as Force loss) do not change.
A hit captive is immediately lost (even during battle).
For the Lost function, captives forfeit values are affected by global modifiers (e.g. Insurrection) and modifiers that affect captives (e.g. Lieutenant Sheckil).

front.title: Hunt Down And Destroy The Jedi / Their Fire Has Gone Out Of The Universe
front.gametext: Hunt Down And Destroy The Jedi:Deploy Holotheatre and Visage Of The Emperor. May deploy Meditation Chamber and/or Epic Duel.{While} this side up, during your move phase, may use 4 Force to take Vader into hand from a location you control (cards on him go to owner's Used Pile). Add 4 to each player's destiny draw for Sense and Alter.{Flip} this card if Vader is at a battleground site and no Light Jedi or Luke is at a battleground site.{Place} out of play if you play Scanning Crew, initiate a non-Epic duel or Force drain at an Executor site.Their Fire Has Gone Out Of The Universe:{While} this side up, opponent cannot initiate battles or Force drains where opponent has a Jedi or Skywalker. You lose no Force from Visage Of The Emperor. While Vader at Meditation Chamber, subtract 2 from each of opponent's battle destiny draws. Opponent may not play Sense or Alter.{Flip} this card if opponent has Luke or a Jedi at a battleground site or if Vader is not on table.{Place} out of play if you play Scanning Crew, initiate a non-Epic duel or Force drain at an Executor site.

back.title: Hunt Down And Destroy The Jedi / Their Fire Has Gone Out Of The Universe
back.gametext: Hunt Down And Destroy The Jedi:Deploy Holotheatre and Visage Of The Emperor. May deploy Meditation Chamber and/or Epic Duel.{While} this side up, during your move phase, may use 4 Force to take Vader into hand from a location you control (cards on him go to owner's Used Pile). Add 4 to each player's destiny draw for Sense and Alter.{Flip} this card if Vader is at a battleground site and no Light Jedi or Luke is at a battleground site.{Place} out of play if you play Scanning Crew, initiate a non-Epic duel or Force drain at an Executor site.Their Fire Has Gone Out Of The Universe:{While} this side up, opponent cannot initiate battles or Force drains where opponent has a Jedi or Skywalker. You lose no Force from Visage Of The Emperor. While Vader at Meditation Chamber, subtract 2 from each of opponent's battle destiny draws. Opponent may not play Sense or Alter.{Flip} this card if opponent has Luke or a Jedi at a battleground site or if Vader is not on table.{Place} out of play if you play Scanning Crew, initiate a non-Epic duel or Force drain at an Executor site.

rulings: Dark does not lose 2 Force to deploy Visage Of The Emperor at the start of the game.
Dark does not lose 2 Force to deploy Visage Of The Emperor when this Objective is on the 7 side.

front.title: •Hunting Party
front.gametext: During your control phase, form a search party for an opponent's missing character at same site. Add 1 to search party destiny draw for each bounty hunter in search party. If successful, capture the character found.
front.lore: Sometimes a missing person is found by the wrong search party.

combo: Hunting Party + Sandwhirl First you spin them around, then you bag them.
Hunting Party + Skiffs As the missing people will be in the desert, most likely, you'll need some cheap, fast landspeed to shuttle your bounty hunters around in.

front.title: •Hunting Party (V)
front.gametext: During your control phase, if your bounty hunter or Trandoshan is escorting a non-frozen captive at a battleground site you control, opponent loses 1 Force. OR If your bounty hunter or Trandoshan just captured a character, opponent loses 1 Force. (Immune to Sense.)
front.lore: Sometimes a missing person is found by the wrong search party.

combo: Hunting Party + Sandwhirl First you spin them around, then you bag them.
Hunting Party + Skiffs As the missing people will be in the desert, most likely, you'll need some cheap, fast landspeed to shuttle your bounty hunters around in.

front.title: •Hutt Bounty
front.gametext: Deploy on an opponent's smuggler, gambler, or thief. If subsequently captured, seized by a bounty hunter and then transfered to Jabba's Palace Dungeon, retrieve Force equal to character's forfeit (+6 if Han) and lose effect. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'Chissaa, picha gawanki Chewbacca. Yupon cogorato kama walpa kyess kashung kawa Wookiee.'

front.title: •Hutt Influence
front.gametext: Deploy on table. Opponent may not cancel or modify Force drains at each Tatooine battleground site where you have two aliens with different card titles. Also, attrition against you is reduced by 2 when two of your non-unique aliens with different card titles are in battle.
front.lore: Jabba's criminal empire extends to all reaches of the Outer Rim.

front.title: •Hutt Smooch
front.gametext: Capture one opponents undercover spy ('cover is broken'). OR if opponent just deployed a spy to a site where opponent has no presence or Force icons, return spy to hand. Any Force used to deploy the spy remains used, and spy may not deploy this turn.
front.lore: 'We have powerful friends. You're gonna regret this.' 'Rota go ma namatota.'

front.title: Hyperoute Navigation Chart
front.gametext: [0] Corscant [1] Carida, Corellia, Eriadu, Kirdo III, Kuat [2] Alderaan, Bothuwui, Kiffex, Rendili, Tibrin, Wakeelmui [3] Malastare, Nal Hutta, Raithal, Ralltiir [4] Aquaris, Chandrila, Corulag, Yavin 4* [5] Anoat, Dantooine, Hoth*, Naboo [6] Bespin, Fondor, Kashyyyk, Mon Calamari [7] Clak'dor VII, Ord Mantell, Roche, Sullust, Tatooine [8] Endor, Kessel [9] Dagobah, Gall * Known Rebel Base

front.title: Hyperwave Scan
front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Scanning Crew is immune to Sense. If Scanning Crew is played against an opponent who has 13 or more cards in hand, opponent also loses all cards with 'Rebel' in the title found there.
front.lore: Full Imperial scans include full-spectrum transceivers, dedicated energy receptors, crystal gravfield traps, and hyperwave signal interceptors.

combo: Hyperwave Scan + Wyron Serper Add 2 to the destiny of this card.

front.title: Hypo
front.gametext: Deploy on your IT-O. Once during each of your control phases, if present with a captive: You may ask one yes-or-no question about cards in opponent's hand. Opponent must answer truthfully or lose 1 Force. OR May add 1 to Force drain where present.
front.lore: Truth drugs like Bavo Six decrease resistance to interrogation. The enormous needle adds psychological pressure, facilitating the interrogation process.

rulings: The requirement of being with a captive applies to both the yes-no question option and the add 1 to Force drain option.
Does not work with frozen captives.
May only choose one option each turn.
If stolen by Light, neither option may be used.

front.title: •I Am Your Father
front.gametext: If Vader just won a battle or duel against a Luke of ability < 6, deploy on Luke. During each of your move phases, opponent loses 2 Force. Also, when at same location as Vader, Luke is power and forfeit = 0 and does not add power to any starships he pilots.
front.lore: 'Search your feelings, you know it to be true.'

combo: I Am Your Father + Mostly Armless

front.title: •I Am Your Father (V)
front.gametext: Deploy on table. [Death Star 2] Vader is deploy = 6. Once per turn, may deploy Vader's Lightsaber from Reserve Deck; reshuffle (or lose 1 Force to deploy from Lost Pile). Whenever a lightsaber swung by Vader 'hits' a character, opponent loses 1 Force. Immune to NOOOOOOOOOOOO!. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'Search your feelings, you know it to be true.'

front.title: •I Can't Shake Him!
front.gametext: If your starship weapon aboard your starfighter was just fired during a battle, add one battle destiny. OR During your deploy phase, deploy one starship weapon or tractor beam from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: 'You've picked one up... watch it!'

front.title: •I Can't Shake Him! (V)
front.gametext: For remainder of turn, opponent must first use 1 Force to fire a weapon and opponent's starship weapon destiny draws are -1. OR During opponent's deploy phase, deploy an Imperial of ability < 3 (except an admiral) aboard your starship from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: 'You've picked one up... watch it!'

pulls: An Imperial of ability < 3 (except an admiral) aboard your starship
rulings: First function affects all opponent's weapons, not a specific target weapon.
First function may be played even if opponent currently has no weapons on table.

front.title: I Find Your Lack Of Faith Disturbing
front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on one of your Dark Jedi. Opponent's total ability at same location is reduced by 2, unless an opponent's Jedi is also present.
front.lore: Darth Vader ruthlessly used the Force to strike down enemies and soldiers who displeased him. He could choke victims from afar without touching them.

front.title: •I Find Your Lack Of Faith Disturbing (V)
front.gametext: Plays on table. Goo Nee Tay is canceled. Unless Deep Hatred on table, opponent may use only one combat card per turn. We'll Handle This may target only Undercover spies and 5D6-RA-7.
front.lore: Darth Vader ruthlessly used the Force to strike down enemies and soldiers who displeased him. He could choke victims from afar without touching them.

front.title: •I Had No Choice
front.gametext: Deploy on an opponent's gambler. Cancels gambler's game text. If a battle was just initiated, you may use X Force to exclude gambler from that battle, where X = gambler's ability.
front.lore: Gamblers are vulnerable to bribery, extortion and other forms of manipulation. Their notorious dealings can be easily taken advantage of.

front.title: I Have You Now
front.gametext: If a Dark Jedi and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle, you may add one battle destiny (add two destiny if Rebel is Luke)
front.lore: 'Several fighters have broken off from the main group. Come with me.' Darth Vader targets his TIE fighter's fire-linked blaster cannons at the Rebel pilots in the trench.

canceledBy: The Force Is Strong With This One (V)

front.title: •I Never Ask That Question
front.gametext: If opponent just played an Interrupt, use 2 Force to deploy on table and stack that card here. If opponent just drew destiny (or played an Interrupt) with the same card title as card here, they lose 1 Force. (Immune to Control)
front.lore: Blank.

front.title: I Want That Map / And Now You'll Give It To Me
front.gametext: I Want That Map:Deploy Tuanul Village, any other [Episode VII] location, and I Will Finish What You Started. Opponent may reveal a unique (•) Resistance character from Reserve Deck; that card is a Resistance Agent. Otherwise, Luke is a Resistance Agent and loses immunity to attrition.{For} remainder of game, non-[Episode VII] Dark Jedi are lost and Resistance Agents are immune to Set For Stun.{Flip} this card if your First Order characters control two battlegrounds and a Resistance Agent is not present at a battleground site.And Now You'll Give It To Me:{While} this side up, where you have a First Order leader, opponent must first use or lose 1 Force to draw a card for battle destiny. Unless BB-8 on table, opponent's Force retrieval is canceled. If Kylo on table: During your turn, may stack an Interrupt from your Lost Pile face up on I Will Finish What You Started; and once per turn, may play an Interrupt stacked there as if from hand (then place that card out of play).{Flip} this card if you do not occupy two battlegrounds or if a Resistance Agent is present at a battleground site.

back.title: I Want That Map / And Now You'll Give It To Me
back.gametext: I Want That Map:Deploy Tuanul Village, any other [Episode VII] location, and I Will Finish What You Started. Opponent may reveal a unique (•) Resistance character from Reserve Deck; that card is a Resistance Agent. Otherwise, Luke is a Resistance Agent and loses immunity to attrition.{For} remainder of game, non-[Episode VII] Dark Jedi are lost and Resistance Agents are immune to Set For Stun.{Flip} this card if your First Order characters control two battlegrounds and a Resistance Agent is not present at a battleground site.And Now You'll Give It To Me:{While} this side up, where you have a First Order leader, opponent must first use or lose 1 Force to draw a card for battle destiny. Unless BB-8 on table, opponent's Force retrieval is canceled. If Kylo on table: During your turn, may stack an Interrupt from your Lost Pile face up on I Will Finish What You Started; and once per turn, may play an Interrupt stacked there as if from hand (then place that card out of play).{Flip} this card if you do not occupy two battlegrounds or if a Resistance Agent is present at a battleground site.

rulings: If Light chooses a Resistance Agent, only cards with that same title are a Resistance Agent.
If no choice is made, all Luke persona cards are a Resistance Agent. They do not become Resistance character cards.

front.title: •I Want That Ship
front.gametext: Deploy on one opponent's unique (•) starship at a location you do not occupy. When starship is targeted by any tractor beam or ion cannon, subtract 2 from maneuver. If starship is captured or lost, lose Effect and opponent must lose 3 Force (5 if Falcon).
front.lore: Like nerf herders herding nerfs, Imperial commanders often use TIE fighters to drive fleeing Rebel ships into tractor beam range.

front.title: •I Will Find Them Quickly, Master
front.gametext: Deploy on table. Opponent may deploy Amidala from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. If Maul present with Amidala and opponent has no Jedi there, she is captured. Once per game may take If The Trace Was Correct into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Utilizing his 'dark eye' probe droids and sensory equipment, Maul knew he would eventually find his target.

front.title: •I Will Finish What You Started
front.gametext: Deploy on table. Vader is lost. Once per turn, may stack an Interrupt from hand face up here to cancel a just drawn weapon destiny at Kylo's site. Kylo is power +1 for each card here. Once per game, may deploy a lightsaber from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Blank.

front.title: •Iasa, The Traitor Of Jawa Canyon
front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. When firing any Jawa weapon, subtracts 3 from target's defense value. When playing Dune Sea Sabacc, may subtract 1 from or add 1 to your total.
front.lore: While on a trip, King Kalit entrusted his credits, sandcrawler and mate to his friend Iasa. When Kalit returned, one was spent, one was sold and the other was missing.

pulledBy: Herat to deploy to same location
combo: Iasa, The Traitor Of Jawa Canyon + Dune Sea Sabacc

front.title: •Ice Storm
front.gametext: Deploy at outermost marker. All characters present at same exterior site are missing. Each turn, during your control phase, storm moves to next marker, reversing direction if at innermost marker. Mobile Effect lost when moved beyond outermost marker.
front.lore: Among the gravest dangers in the harsh environment of Hoth are frequent quick-moving ice storms.

rulings: Will deploy and move to/from Wampa Cave like any other marker site. Does not cause characters at Wampa Cave to go missing.
May be canceled during the response step, such as by Control, in which case it will be canceled without making any characters missing.

front.title: •I'd Just As Soon Kiss A Wookiee
front.gametext: Use 3 Force to place an opponent's just deployed character, starship, vehicle, weapon, or device in opponent's hand. On opponent's next turn, that card (or one card of same title) may deploy for free.
front.lore: 'I can arrange that. You could USE a good kiss!'

rulings: The target does deploy briefly, triggering any automatic actions (such as Objective flips) first.
The target card is placed in owner's hand, even if it was being deployed from Reserve Deck or somewhere else.
If two cards were being deployed simultaneously, such as via Squadron Assignments, both cards are equally affected (both placed in hand and may deploy free next turn).
If the target card is unique, that unique card/persona cannot deploy again this turn.

front.title: •If The Trace Was Correct
front.gametext: Deploy on I Will Find Them Quickly, Master. Once during each of your deploy phases may deploy a Sith Probe Droid from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. If Amidala forfeited at same site as Maul, she is captured instead of lost. While Maul escorting Amidala, opponent's battle destiny draws are -1 and during your turn you may use up to 3 Force in opponent's Force Pile. While Maul escorting Amidala at a non-Tatooine battleground site, opponent's Force drains at Tatooine sites are -1 and at the end of every turn, may reshuffle opponent's Reserve Deck.

front.title: •••IG MagnaGuard
front.gametext: Grievous is defense value +2 here. While aboard Invisible Hand, draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise and characters here are immune to Clash Of Sabers.
front.lore: Assassin. Trade Federation.

front.title: •IG-2000
front.gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 2 passengers. Maneuver +3 and immune to attrition < 3 if IG-88 piloting. Ion Cannon may deploy aboard.
front.lore: IG-88's assault starfighter. Custom designed. Boasts a Kuat Galaxy-15 engine from a Nebulon-B frigate. Heavy ion cannon often used to disable starships before boarding.

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.title: •IG-88
front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May 'assassinate' any character at same site hit by IG-88 (victim is immediately lost). May use two different weapons. May initiate battle and be battled. Immune to Restraining Bolt and purchase.
front.lore: Bounty hunter. Went berserk upon activation. Murdered all designers at Holowan Mechanicals. IG-88's outstanding 'dismantle on sight' warrant ignored by Darth Vader.

front.title: •IG-88 (V)
front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May use two weapons. Once per turn, if escorting a captive, may take any one card from Force Pile into hand; reshuffle. May lose 1 Force to cancel a just drawn weapon destiny targeting IG-88. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Bounty hunter. Went berserk upon activation. Murdered all designers at Holowan Mechanicals. IG-88's outstanding 'dismantle on sight' warrant ignored by Darth Vader.

rulings: A destiny targets IG-88 (V) if it is used in comparison with a number on the IG-88 (V) card, such as his armor.
The destiny drawn for the weapon Booma does not target IG-88 (V).

front.title: •IG-88 In IG-2000
front.gametext: May add 2 passengers. Permanent pilot is •IG-88, who adds 2 to power and 3 to maneuver. May initiate battle. When in a battle you initiate, adds one battle destiny. Ion Cannon may deploy aboard.
front.lore: Starship adapted to the assassin droid's specifications. Flight controls linked directly to processing unit. Real-time relays minimize response time.

front.title: •IG-88 With Riot Gun
front.gametext: May initiate battle. Permanent weapon is riot gun (may target a character for free; draw destiny; target captured if destiny +1 > defense value). Adds one battle destiny if alone or with your other bounty hunter. Immune to Restraining Bolt and purchase.
front.lore: Bounty hunter droid equipped with proprietary stealth technology. Archived several of its enhancement subroutines in favor of sophisticated tracking and capture programming.

front.title: •IG-88's Neural Inhibitor
front.gametext: Deploy on IG-88, or use 2 Force on any other bounty hunter. May target a non-droid character using 3 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny +1 > ability, until end of your next turn character is power, forfeit and landspeed = 0.
front.lore: Menotor DAS-430 electromagnetic projectile launcher. Often mistaken for a blaster rifle. Fires small hollow darts filled with neurotoxin which cause temporary paralysis.

front.title: •IG-88's Pulse Cannon
front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on IG-88, 4 on your other warrior. Adds 2 to power. May target X non-droid characters or creatures using X Force. Draw destiny for each. If destiny = 0, character is power -1 and forfeit -1 until end of turn. If destiny -1 > defense value, target hit.
front.lore: IG-88's personal favorite for mass destruction. Rapid-fire fusion plasma bursts are extremely effective against multiple targets. Not widely used due to incidental damage.

front.title: •I'm On The Leader
front.gametext: Target opponent's starfighter making an Attack Run. Draw destiny. Add 1 for each of your TIEs in Death Star: Trench. If total destiny > maneuver, starfighter is lost. OR Add 1 to weapon destiny draws of any starfighter for remainder of this turn.
front.lore: In the defense of the Death Star at the Battle of Yavin, Darth Vader took the lead attacker, supported by his wingmen Black 2 and Black 3.

front.title: •I'm Sorry
front.gametext: Deploy on table. If This Deal Is Getting Worse All The Time on table, once per game may take up to 2 interior Cloud City battlegrounds into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. You may not play Scanning Crew or Imperial Barrier. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'I'm sorry, too.'

front.title: IM4-099 (Eyeemmfour)
front.gametext: Whenever opponent Force drains at same or adjacent site, may deploy up to four troopers there as a 'react.' When IM4 is present with your trooper, Rebels are deploy +2 to same site and opponent may not 'react' to or from same site.
front.lore: Imperial Mark IV Patrol Droid. Identifies criminal activity and transmits information to local authorities. Monitors random comm signals for illegal activity.

front.title: •Image Of The Dark Lord
front.gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy at any site if opponent is generating at least 3 Force more than you. At that site, adjacent sites and same site as Vader, players activate Force only if they have presence.
front.lore: Vader's hologram exacts loyalty from his legions.

front.title: •Image Of The Dark Lord (V)
front.gametext: Deploy on a planet site. Opponent's Force drains are -1 here (-2 if Vader controls an adjacent site).
front.lore: Vader's hologram exacts loyalty from his legions.

front.title: •Imbalance
front.gametext: If opponent just retrieved Force, opponent must lose X Force, where X = one-half the number of cards retrieved (round up).
front.lore: 'ConcentraaAAATE!'

front.title: •Imbalance & •Kintan Strider
front.gametext: Cancel Blaster Proficiency. (Immune to Sense.) OR If opponent just retrieved Force, opponent must lose X Force, where X = one-half the number of cards retrieved (round down) to a minimum of 1. OR If opponent's character just lost, lose 1 Force to retrieve the topmost character of ability < 6 (except a [Maintenance] or [Permanent Weapon] card) in your Lost Pile into hand.

cancels: Sorry About The Mess & Blaster Proficiency

front.title: •Imperial Academy Training
front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Each of your non-unique Imperials armed with a non-unique blaster is forfeit +2, adds 1 to his total weapon destiny and, where present, cumulatively adds 1 to total battle destiny. (Immune to Alter while your non-unique blaster is on table.)
front.lore: Graduates of the Empire's military academies train to fire standard-issue weapons efficiently.

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.title: •Imperial Arrest Order
front.gametext: Deploy on table. Unique (•) Imperials of ability < 3 are forfeit +2. Nabrun Leids and Elis Helrot are limited to owner's move phase and exterior sites. Once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one docking bay from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: When an Imperial blockade raises the alert level, all independent ships are scanned and any suspicious characters on planet are detained and interrogated.

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.title: •Imperial Arrest Order & •Secret Plans
front.gametext: Deploy on table. Unique (•) Imperials of ability < 3 are forfeit +1. Nabrun Leids and Elis Helrot are limited to owner's move phase and exterior sites only.
